                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1302">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860H.01/9–1644: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Political Adviser on the Staff of the
                        Supreme Allied Commander, Mediterranean Theater</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caserta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-16T09:00:00+02:00"
                            >September 16, 1944—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 3:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>405. Second Partisan corps in course of its present offensive in Serbia has
                    overrun General Mihailovich’s HQS. General is reported to have escaped although
                    his documents apparently fell into Partisan hands. British Liaison Officer
                    accompanying Partisans has been asked to submit full report immediately. He has
                    been warned that it is essential element of Allied policy that arms are not sent
                    to Tito for <pb facs="1418" n="1408" xml:id="pg_1408"/> purpose of fighting
                    Chetniks unless latter are actively obstructing Partisan forces from reaching
                    legitimate military objectives or are actively collaborating with enemy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
